race.comment: RAYLANA (12) disappointed two back before a better run last start at Pinjarra over 1406m. She looks to be trending the right way this time in work and getting away from the inside looks ideal. Has scope for further improvement and she can knock over her maiden win. LUNA ASCENDING (11) flew home two back before a 2.2L defeat last start on the Scarpside at Pinjarra. The rise in trip now looks ideal for her and she rates highly on her recent form. Likely to get back in the run once again, but can go to the next level now. DANCING SPIRIT (13) was strong fresh before a disappointing performance over 1100m here most recently. Pike remains in the saddle and the rise in trip can see her improve. Can sit handier this time and can make her presence felt. GOLD ENIGMA (10) can be in the finish on resumption. DUKES SPIRIT (5) is not out of this first-up with a couple of trials under his belt.
